General Information On The Risk of Disk Failure
Mirror Of Memory Block 1 (Redundancy of Storage)
- Tradeoff in memory overhead versus strong data integrity.
Block Corruptions are detected through checksum algorithms
which reads the data of a memory block and outputs a summary of the data.
It can detect if data has been corrupted in a memory block.
